CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 29, 1955, pg. 25, reads: "Future Champs? - These boxers will take part in series of exhibition bouts slated for Wadsworth Hall Friday night. All are promising amateurs. Left to right, back row: Kid Spicer, Harry Etheridge and Robert Lee Reeves.  Middle row: Marx, Flourney and Carl Jordan.  In the front are Milliard Glenn, Earl Johnson, team coach, ad Ronald Burke. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of boxing coach Earl Johnson squatting in center, and seven boxers including front row left to right: Millard Glenn, Ronald Burke; second row: Marx, Flourney, and Carl Jordan; back row: Kid Spicer, Harry Etheridge, and Robert Lee Reeves, posed in gymnasium
